cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on analyzing job hopping behavior and talent flow patterns using data from online professional networks. This falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as well as data analytics (cs.CY). The paper also involves studying job promotion/demotion, which could fall under the category of software development (cs.SD) or social and economic systems (cs.SOC). Lastly, the paper involves connectivity analysis, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
